cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SE, cs.DS, cs.DB 

This paper deals with the security of user credentials and proposes new protocols for checking compromised credentials. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses operational requirements and threat models, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). The empirical analysis and experimentation could also fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases).
